    public interface SearchableConfigurable
extends Configurable
    SearchableConfigurable instances would be instantiated on buildSearchableOptions step during Installer's build to index of all available options. TraverseUIStarter

    • Method Detail

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        Unique configurable id. Note this id should be THE SAME as the one specified in XML.
        See Also:
        ConfigurableEP.id

      • enableSearch

        default java.lang.Runnable enableSearch(java.lang.String option)
        Parameters:
        option - setting search query
        Returns:
        an action to perform when this configurable is opened when a search filter query is entered by the user in setting dialog. This action, for example, can select something in a tree or a list embedded in this setting page that matches the query.

      • getOriginalClass

        default java.lang.Class<?> getOriginalClass()
        When building an index of searchable options, it's important to know a class which caused the creation of a configurable. It often happens that the configurable is created based on a provider from an arbitrary extension point. In such a case, the provider's class should be returned from this method.
        When the configurable is based on several providers consider extending CompositeConfigurable.
        Keep in mind that this method can be expensive as it can load previously unloaded class.
        Returns:
        a class which is a cause of the creation of this configurable
